## 4 Discussion on related work

Classifier-free guidance (CFG) , first proposed as a replacement for classifier guidance (CG)  is controlled by a scale parameter. The higher we set classifier-free guidance, the more we get faithful, high-quality images. However, it requires external labels, such as text  or class  labels, making it impossible to apply to unconditional diffusion models. Also, it requires specific traning procedure with label dropping and it is known that high CFG causes saturation .

