## 6 Conclusion, limitations and societal impacts

ConclusionWe introduce Smoothed Energy Guidance (SEG), a novel training- and condition-free guidance method for image generation with diffusion models. The key advantages of SEG lie in its flexibility and the theoretical foundation, allowing us to significantly enhance sample quality without side effects by adjusting the standard deviation of the Gaussian filter. We hope our method inspires further research on improving generative models, and extending the approach beyond image generation, for example, to video or natural language processing.

Limitations and societal impactsThe paper proposes guidance to enhance quality outcomes. Consequently, the attainable quality of our approach is contingent upon the baseline model employed. Furthermore, the application of SEG to temporal attention mechanisms in video or multi-view diffusion models is not addressed, remaining a promising avenue for future research. It is important to note that the improvements achieved through this method may potentially lead to unintended negative societal consequences by inadvertently amplifying existing stereotypes or harmful biases.